The paper focuses on examining the effectiveness of mobile game-based learning compared to traditional online learning to thwart phishing threats. This involves studying user behavior and interaction with technology, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also deals with cybersecurity and fraud prevention, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper involves the use of technology to enhance learning, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Graphics (cs.GR).
